@shawndbarber ‘s passion for his work is palpable. When he’s not documentation tattoo history through his masterful paintings of the most important tattoo artists of our time he’s working at his Los Angeles tattoo shop, @memoirtattoo . He has a way of describing the feelings in and around tattoo art like no one I’ve ever been around and his passion is easily seen through both his paintings and his tattoos. Filming the piece on him for @pirateandpalm was one of my favorite projects that I have ever worked on and this is tiny a snippet from our interview for that film.

I’m happy to share a recent painting for @four8wineworks for their LEGION wine label. The bottle drops tomorrow, 9/8. Only available at Four 8 Wineworks in Jerome and Old Town Cottonwood.

For those of you collecting the various label art on LEGION by Four 8 Wineworks, the next featured artist is Shawn Barber @shawndbarber . Shawn has worked on several @puscifer projects along with his extensive body of work (see his poster design in photo 2). Shawn and fellow LEGION label artist, @kimsaigh opened Memoir Tattoo in 2009.

The 4th and final LEGION label from this vintage will be released on October 6 (the same day as the opening of the new @merkinvineyards Hilltop Trattoria). Be one of the lucky few to get all 4. We still have a limited quantity of the first label in this series by @danielmartindiaz . Grapes first. State last. Just getting back home from a memorable and epic tattoo convention @richmondtattooconvention ! This was an inspiring weekend with old and new friends, the first floor was buzzing, you could feel the electricity in the room. Tons of happy faces and amazing stories from tattooing past and present. I can’t thank @jdcrowetattoos and @jessesmithtattoos for putting together the best show I’ve been to in the states in a long time. Please do this again!!!

Had a blast all weekend @richmondtattooconvention doing some live alla prima portrait painting and a few tattoos! Thanks to everyone that sat for a portrait, got tattooed and bought some art.
A memorable and inspiring weekend like no other. Thanks to @jdcrowetattoos and @jessesmithtattoos for the amazing weekend.

It’s been such and honor and a huge treat for us to have this legend (and friend), Mark Mahoney , join us for a few days, while he transitions into his new, private studio. Needless to say, Shawn and I, and our coworkers are all over the moon, to have this opportunity to work alongside Mark, watch him work, and hear his fantastic stories. While endings are often sad, new beginnings can be just as exciting, and we wish Mark and Nicole all the best in their move to the new space. Love you guys.. @markmahoney_ssc @nicmahoney @shamrocksocialclub
